1
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,583
[music playing]

2
00:00:27,708 --> 00:00:29,791
Oh, hey. Who're you?

3
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:35,625
[WOMAN]
Pardon me, Mamechiyo.

4
00:00:35,708 --> 00:00:37,375
--Mmm?
--It appears that the captain

5
00:00:37,458 --> 00:00:39,625
of the Kamogawa Rockrs
has been returned.

6
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:13,333
[MISA] A bit of a treat
for saving me.

7
00:02:13,416 --> 00:02:14,958
Ah!

8
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:17,250
Guys, we didn't
actually do anything.

9
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:19,791
True, Shuten said
you could leave.

10
00:02:19,875 --> 00:02:21,291
--It wasn't anything we did.
--Ah!

11
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:22,875
What she means to say is,

12
00:02:22,958 --> 00:02:24,375
it may not
have looked like much,

13
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,041
but we rescued you
from Shuten's gang

14
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:27,750
and basically saved
the festival, right?

15
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:28,916
Mm-hmm.

16
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,083
That means one stone
for us! Woo!

17
00:02:31,166 --> 00:02:33,166
[MISA] Doji Shuten
is still up to something,

18
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:35,250
but it'll be all right.

19
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:38,416
Concert security
should be able to--

20
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:39,916
Mmm. Mmm!

21
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:45,916
Nice bracelet. What's that charm
you have on it?

22
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,541
Is it a Moonlight--
sorry, I mean a jinxed stone?

23
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:52,625
[chuckles]
A jinxed stone, yes.

24
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:54,333
People say
they bring illness and death

25
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:55,708
to the ones who possess them.

26
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:58,000
--Really?
--[chuckles]

27
00:02:58,083 --> 00:03:00,291
Only superstition,
I'm sure.

28
00:03:00,375 --> 00:03:02,458
--Look over there.
--[NOZOMI] Huh?

29
00:03:02,541 --> 00:03:04,958
Oh, hey. Doesn't that
look like Mamechiyo?

30
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:06,541
[YUKINA]
She's kinda staring at us.

31
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:08,708
[AI] Do you think
we should invite her over here?

32
00:03:08,791 --> 00:03:10,291
Hey, there! If you wan--

33
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:12,583
Please pretend
you didn't notice her.

34
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:15,041
She actually thinks
she's being quite stealthy.

35
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:16,208
Wow, it's a maiko!

36
00:03:16,291 --> 00:03:18,916
Oi, mates!
We could use some help here.

37
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,541
Are any of you good at drawing?

38
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,708
[SHEENA] This is all that's
finished on the program cover.

39
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:25,458
Ebisu, the guitarist,
was working on it,

40
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,791
but he's gonna be out of
commission for a while.

41
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:29,625
Yukina, why don't
you finish it up?

42
00:03:29,708 --> 00:03:31,333
With the sketches
already done,

43
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:32,541
it shouldn't be
too difficult to do!

44
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:34,333
[BOTH]
Oh, really?

45
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:35,708
A clean-up job?

46
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:38,541
I think I should be able
to handle that for you guys.

47
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:40,958
[grunts, pants]

48
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:43,708
-Um. Mamechiyo, was it?
-What are you doing here?

49
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,166
Uh... ooh.

50
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:49,333
[gasps, grunts]

51
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:52,583
Are you trying
to become friends with Misa?

52
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:55,083
--[GROUP] Huh?
--[breathing angrily]

53
00:03:55,166 --> 00:03:57,375
No! I most certainly am not!

54
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:03,250
[sighs]

55
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:06,208
[YUKINA] I don't understand.
I thought it looked pretty good.

56
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:09,875
[ALL] Uh...

57
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,791
Well, we could always go
with a silhouette.

58
00:04:12,875 --> 00:04:15,625
Maybe they just wanted you
to follow the sketch more.

59
00:04:15,708 --> 00:04:18,666
Yeah, I figured.
That's what I was trying to do.

60
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,416
--Uh...
--Don't worry about it.

61
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,291
I'm used to this
kind of thing.

62
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:24,458
[BOTH laugh nervously]

63
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:27,875
--Come on, Yukippe. Let's go.
--Go where?

64
00:04:33,666 --> 00:04:36,083
--[AI] Whoa, look at me!
--[NOZOMI] I know! Totally cute!

65
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,500
[clicking]

66
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,583
[MOMIYAMA] No. Unfortunately,
I couldn't find Chiaya.

67
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:54,375
But I did notice the Shuten gang
on Mount Oe acting suspiciously.

68
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:57,083
The Hall
of the Lotus Queen, huh?

69
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:59,208
[MOMIYAMA] I thought
you'd want me to look into it.

70
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:01,500
[HARUKA] I can't imagine
what they would be doing.

71
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:04,333
I don't think anyone else
knows how to use the stones.

72
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:05,625
[MOMIYAMA]
Whether they do or not,

73
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,083
I'm sure they're gathering them.

74
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:08,708
If I play my cards right,

75
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:12,458
I may be able to bring
them all back with me.

76
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:15,125
[HARUKA] There's not much time
left until the full moon.

77
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:16,958
Just hurry, all right?

78
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:21,708
[MAMECHIYO] There's still
something I don't understand.

79
00:05:21,791 --> 00:05:23,791
Why kidnap
the Kamogawa captain?

80
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:26,333
[sighs] I told you,
I was only killing time.

81
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:29,083
And did she, perhaps,
say anything about me?

82
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:31,166
--No, not a word.
--[whimpers]

83
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,333
Well. Tell me, Shuten,

84
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:36,916
what surprise have you
prepared for us? Or need I ask?

85
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,791
One of your clever toys,
I suppose?

86
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:41,083
You'll just have to wait
and see like everyone else.

87
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:43,166
--Boo!
--[chuckles]

88
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,416
Scaring Misa
isn't my only objective.

89
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,041
I intend to blow
the entire festival away.

90
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:49,458
Blow it away?

91
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:51,291
Takumi Co.'s
greatest masterpiece,

92
00:05:51,375 --> 00:05:53,750
the Kiyomizu Temple's
fan-shaped stage.

93
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,208
I've joined forces
with some blokes

94
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,375
who are interested
in destroying it.

95
00:05:57,458 --> 00:05:59,083
[humphs]

96
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:01,208
We've modified
the Hall of the Lotus Queen's

97
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,458
Thousand Armed Kannon a touch.

98
00:06:03,541 --> 00:06:05,458
[MAMECHIYO]

99
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:08,125
What's wrong?
I told you I don't hold back

100
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:10,791
when I'm killing time.
This should be interesting.

101
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:15,125
[BOTH laugh]

102
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,833
You're quite the joker!

103
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:19,250
That sense of humor will
get you in trouble some day.

104
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:22,750
Your plan is impossible.
Not to mention dull.

105
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:27,583
--[gasps]
--[echoing] Not to mention dull.

106
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:29,750
[SHUTEN thinks]
"Dull"? Me? "Dull"?

107
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:32,500
Well, we'll see about that.

108
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:35,500
Tell Takumi we need
something more sensational!

109
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,083
[SQUAD]
Yes, sir!

110
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:40,750
[GIRLS moaning]

111
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,250
[TSURUHA] This is unacceptable.

112
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:44,500
We can't have impostors
wandering about.

113
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:46,958
It will undermine the dignity
of the geisha district.

114
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,750
[NOZOMI]
We didn't mean to.

115
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,833
[CHIAYA] We were
just looking for somebody.

116
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,875
[MAMECHIYO]
What is the commotion about?

117
00:06:52,958 --> 00:06:54,500
They were
sitting around in Gion.

118
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,833
We thought it best
to bring them back here.

119
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,250
[CHIAYA gasps]

120
00:07:02,333 --> 00:07:05,583
That looks just like
the other Core.

121
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:08,000
Did you and the Rockrs' captain
have a falling out or something?

122
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:10,416
--No, why?
--She completely blew you off.

123
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,000
And what is that to do with you?

124
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:17,125
Well, was it a misunderstanding?
Maybe there's a reason she--

125
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:18,541
What sort of reason?

126
00:07:18,625 --> 00:07:20,791
Oh. I don't really
know that, exactly.

127
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:22,625
It's just a feeling I had.

128
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:27,375
[MAMECHIYO]
No. I don't think so.

129
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:30,291
[rock music playing]

130
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,500
[no discernible dialog]

131
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:45,208
[pants] I'll need a sec
to catch my breath.

132
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:46,666
I think you need more
than a sec for that.

133
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,666
It's too bad Momizo
isn't singing.

134
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,416
Then it would be
a Momi-Ham reunion!

135
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,916
[MA-BO] Misa! Stop that.

136
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,666
We don't talk about him.

137
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:58,375
Be honest, Ma-bo. You want
to perform again, don't you?

138
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,166
[MA-BO]
Who said that?

139
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,625
[MISA] Han-chan has told me
a few things about the band,

140
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,875
like the real reason
that you guys broke up.

141
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:06,500
He said that there was bad blood

142
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:09,208
because of a member who hit the
road before your major debut.

143
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:11,208
[MA-BO] Why're you
telling people about that?

144
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:14,750
Momizo fired him
without asking us.

145
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,416
There was no good reason to.

146
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,958
Dude would have improved,
given a little time.

147
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:20,541
I'm sure he would.

148
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,083
[HAN-CHAN] "A real rocker will
come back and prove his worth."

149
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:25,208
That's how Momizo felt about it.

150
00:08:25,291 --> 00:08:27,333
[MA-BO]
And I disagreed, but whatever.

151
00:08:27,416 --> 00:08:30,333
In the end, I still wanted us
to play together.

152
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:31,791
There you have it.

153
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,666
That's why I could never
get rid of these sideburns.

154
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,208
[humphs]

155
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:43,333
[BOTH snoring]

156
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:45,958
I miss you, too.

157
00:08:58,750 --> 00:08:59,833
[AI]
Whoa!

158
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:13,333
Are these
really Misa's memories?

159
00:09:13,416 --> 00:09:14,500
--Yeah.
--No way.

160
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:15,958
Where did you get that camera?

161
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:18,333
It looks like they used
to be really good friends.

162
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,083
They sure aren't anymore.
What happened?

163
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:21,625
Hey, how much did it cost?

164
00:09:23,708 --> 00:09:26,333
There must be something we can
do to help them reconcile.

165
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:30,416
[GIRLS snoring]

166
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:35,875
[AI moans]

167
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:49,166
Oh!

168
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,583
[JOHNNY] Blimey!
Someone stole your pick?

169
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:03,041
[moans]

170
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:05,291
[SHEENA] It was important
to you, wasn't it, Captain?

171
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:08,250
[grunts]
Yeah, but I'll be okay.

172
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,791
How's everybody else?

173
00:10:09,875 --> 00:10:12,125
Ready to go, I hope.
We've got a big day.

174
00:10:12,208 --> 00:10:14,500
--[SHIDO] Captain!
--[JOHNNY] Oh no!

175
00:10:14,583 --> 00:10:16,291
[NOZOMI]
We'll look for it for you.

176
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,666
We saw it taken. We can help!

177
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,875
--[GROUP gasps]
--You saw who took the pick?

178
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,125
Well, no. It was dark,

179
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:25,333
but we did see them fall
and hit their forehead.

180
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:28,208
So, one look at their face,
and we should be able to tell.

181
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:30,833
[NOZOMI] You guys please keep
getting ready for the festival.

182
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:33,458
--You sure you got it?
--Yes!

183
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:39,875
--[rock music playing]
--[CROWD chattering]

184
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:48,916
[CROWD cheering]

185
00:10:57,041 --> 00:10:58,416
[sighs]

186
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,708
[thunder rumbling]

187
00:11:03,666 --> 00:11:05,708
[BOTH gasp]

188
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:10,416
Beautiful, aren't they?

189
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,625
And now,
we'll always be best mates!

190
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:13,958
Yes.

191
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:16,125
[MISA] Even your maiko training
won't change that.

192
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,166
If this is to be
my only contest,

193
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,666
I just want us
to perform our best.

194
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,083
Yeah, me too.

195
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:24,375
--[CROWD cheering]
--[gasps]

196
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:32,125
She's never coming back to me.

197
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:34,583
She has forgotten me entirely.

198
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:42,041
Oh, hi, Mamechiyo.

199
00:11:44,875 --> 00:11:45,875
[GIRLS gasp]

200
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:47,708
Hey! What did
you just throw in there?

201
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,458
Were those the stones?

202
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:50,500
Why?

203
00:11:50,583 --> 00:11:52,500
I was tired of looking at them.

204
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:57,375
Without that, the captain
won't be able to do anything!

205
00:11:57,458 --> 00:11:59,416
Isn't it the same for you?

206
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,000
And you know,
there are people

207
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:03,125
who would have been happy
to have that!

208
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:05,416
Around here, you think?

209
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,875
Mmm, little more
to the right, maybe?

210
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:09,958
Wait, what did you mean?

211
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:14,500
[rain pattering]

212
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:17,083
[humming]

213
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:18,625
[beeps]

214
00:12:19,958 --> 00:12:20,875
[humphs]

215
00:12:22,291 --> 00:12:23,166
[beeps]

216
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:36,583
You said the captain
can't do anything

217
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:38,375
without the stone.
Can you explain?

218
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:40,416
She's not going to be able
to be a Best now!

219
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:43,541
I actually think
it's pretty self-explanatory

220
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:47,000
Oh, hey! I'm gonna
go look in the boxes.

221
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:48,958
Who knows, right?
Maybe we'll get lucky

222
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,958
and find one in there!
Sure hope so.

223
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:51,916
Huh?

224
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,041
[panting]

225
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:55,791
Hey, give me a ride, will you?

226
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:56,791
[NOZOMI] Huh?

227
00:12:58,375 --> 00:13:00,083
Why don't we all look together?

228
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:01,666
[gasps]

229
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:04,083
--No, thank you. Why should I?
--[NOZOMI] Don't be like that!

230
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:05,791
You just have to make up!

231
00:13:05,875 --> 00:13:07,916
Real friends fight
all the time, you know!

232
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,291
[CHIAYA]
Please help us!

233
00:13:13,708 --> 00:13:17,333
--[rock music playing]
--[CROWD cheering]

234
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:23,333
That rock you always wore.
Was it your sideburns?

235
00:13:34,541 --> 00:13:36,333
[gasps]

236
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,333
[SQUAD chuckles]

237
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:41,208
[SHUTEN] Hello there.
You're the fellow

238
00:13:41,291 --> 00:13:43,333
sniffing around
about the jinxed stones, eh?

239
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:46,208
Sorry to tell you, my friend,
but there aren't any here.

240
00:13:46,291 --> 00:13:48,666
What do you want those
so-called "jinxed" stones for?

241
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,041
Did you know they're--

242
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:51,791
There's somebody
who's collecting them, you see.

243
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:55,041
Oh, wait. Are you looking
for a trip into space, as well?

244
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,416
[grumbles]

245
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,541
[KERUO] Excuse me, sir!
Only-- it's the countdown.

246
00:13:58,625 --> 00:13:59,541
What's wrong?

247
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:00,875
[crackling]

248
00:14:00,958 --> 00:14:02,458
[MOMIYAMA] It looked
like it could be dangerous.

249
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:03,750
I thought maybe
I should stop it.

250
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:05,166
[SHUTEN]
You ruddy bastard!

251
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,166
Now we'll have to fix it!
Bring the user's manual.

252
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:10,333
I'm not going
to let you ruin my fun.

253
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:13,291
[AI] Hmm.

254
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,083
Ooh! I think I got one!

255
00:14:16,166 --> 00:14:17,833
[grunts]

256
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:19,708
Fantastic! Now I'm stuck!

257
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:22,583
Just a thought, but you might
try opening your hand.

258
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:23,875
Right, I got good news!

259
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,583
There's a manual button
for emergencies.

260
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:27,083
--[gasps]
--Well, where is it?

261
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:29,958
[grunting]

262
00:14:33,458 --> 00:14:35,583
Oh, hey, maybe this button
will open it.

263
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:38,500
[BOTH shout]

264
