269
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:58,500
[rumbling]

270
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,375
[SQUAD gasps]

271
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:03,250
[high-pitched humming]

272
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:05,500
[engines start]

273
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:09,375
Gimme a break!
Why isn't it opening?

274
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:10,750
Is it broken?

275
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,416
--[clicking repeatedly]
--C'mon, c'mon, c'mon!

276
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:13,958
--[gasps]
--[groans]

277
00:15:14,041 --> 00:15:17,250
--Hey, stop for a sec, Ai.
--What's up? [yelps]

278
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,458
[MOMIYAMA]
Where's Chiaya Misono?

279
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:25,041
--She's over there?
--[grunts]

280
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:38,666
[gasps]

281
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:42,541
Why's Mother here?

282
00:15:47,625 --> 00:15:48,750
[grunts]

283
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:55,166
[gasps]

284
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:58,541
[BOTH] There they are!

285
00:15:58,625 --> 00:16:00,333
[grunting]

286
00:16:00,416 --> 00:16:02,250
[screaming]

287
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:06,250
[BOTH scream, grunt]

288
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:09,500
[moaning]

289
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:12,875
[KIKUSHINO] I was worried
that little friend of yours

290
00:16:12,958 --> 00:16:14,916
would lead you away
from your true calling.

291
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,666
I spoke to her about it.

292
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:17,833
[gasps]

293
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:22,541
[gasps]

294
00:16:28,666 --> 00:16:31,083
T'was my duty.
Making you into a full geisha

295
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:33,791
is my priority, not looking
after your social life.

296
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:35,375
True, but still--

297
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:37,125
[KIKUSHINO]
That said, I did not imagine

298
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:40,041
that she would distance herself
from you so... thoroughly.

299
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:42,458
A rather simple girl, that one.

300
00:16:42,541 --> 00:16:44,458
[crying]

301
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:49,458
[splashes, sobbing]

302
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:59,791
Now I believe this
to be my path.

303
00:16:59,875 --> 00:17:02,208
I know I was meant
to be a geisha.

304
00:17:02,291 --> 00:17:07,500
But, when I was younger,
honestly, I wished to run away.

305
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:11,083
If Misa hadn't abandoned
our friendship,

306
00:17:11,166 --> 00:17:13,333
I probably would have
remained half-hearted

307
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:15,541
in my dedication to the art.

308
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,625
[sobs]

309
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:21,291
Still, surely there was
another way!

310
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:23,750
Could she not
have explained herself?

311
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:26,250
She refused to say
even a single word to me.

312
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:30,416
She's been waiting all this time
for you to become a geisha.

313
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:36,291
That pick is
all the proof you need.

314
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:38,625
She has kept it close
throughout these past years,

315
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:41,625
hoping for your success.
Does that mean nothing to you?

316
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:54,375
Mamechiyo? Let's go.
We can bring it to her.

317
00:17:55,416 --> 00:17:56,291
[grunts]

318
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:57,625
[loud boom]

319
00:17:57,708 --> 00:17:59,958
[rockets shrieking]

320
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:02,208
[gasps]

321
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:04,958
--Nozomi!
--Big problem!

322
00:18:05,041 --> 00:18:08,083
--[rock music playing]
--[CROWD cheering]

323
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:11,250
--[loud boom]
--[alarm blaring]

324
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,250
[CROWD screams] Huh?

325
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:21,875
[CROWD screaming]

326
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:30,166
[GROUP screams]

327
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:32,625
[CROWD screaming]

328
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:38,791
